The apartment features three bedrooms. The primary bedroom boasts a king-sized bed, a large walk-in closet, and a private balcony on the second floor. Situated in the coveted Bel Air Skycrest neighborhood, this elegantly modern yet traditional-style home was envisioned for grand-scale living and entertaining. Capturing panoramic city, canyon, and mountain views, the home seamlessly blends indoor and outdoor living, offering the ideal space to host family and friends.Arrive to the private drive, where the ivy-clad facade and lush landscaping frame the towering, arched front door. Enter into the magnificent formal living and dining room with soaring 30-foot ceilings, an entertainer's bar, regal fireplace and floor-to-ceiling arched windows and glass doors framing views of the property and mountains beyond. Off the entertaining space is the expansive gourmet chef's kitchen with spacious island, premier Viking appliances and an adjacent family room with fireplace. Glass doors connect living and entertaining spaces to the extraordinary backyard retreat, where tall palms and mature trees hold court over the swimming pool, heated spa, built-in BBQ kitchen and grass yard. Expansive terraces and a covered loggia offer ample space for lounging, dining and entertaining amidst the far-reaching views.Completing the first floor is a plush home theater with a wet bar and an office that may serve as an additional bedroom or staff quarters. Stairs ascend to the sweeping terraced hallway, which overlooks the living room below. At one end, find three bedrooms, each with ensuite baths and walk-in closets, and on the other, the stunning primary suite, boasting a wet bar with fridge, soaring ceiling, marble fireplace, soaking tub and balcony with fantastic views.Featuring a 2-car garage and plenty of additional parking, the home offers a quiet, tranquil setting in a central location close to the Westside and L.A.'s best private schools, including Curtis, Buckley, Mirman and Milken. With convenient nearby access to the 405, the home is minutes from Brentwood, Beverly Hills, Santa Monica and the Valley.

Terracotta floor tiles lead you through under high vaulted ceilings covered in wood. The sunswept kitchen offers views of the backyard, stone countertops, stainless steel appliances, a seated island, and breakfast nook. Adjacent to the kitchen is the dining room and steps leading to a sunken living room with a floor-to-ceiling fireplace. Each of the home's secondary bedrooms have skylights and one has an en suite bath. Outside, the backyard offers a true oasis with a sparkling pool and spa surrounded by lush, mature bamboo and other foliage. Whether you're taking a dip in the pool, lounging on the stone patio or playing on the turf lawn, the backyard is the ideal space for unwinding and enjoying Southern California's year-round sunshine. The property also comes complete with a 2-car garage with a washer and dryer and ample storage space. Combining an idyllic location with timeless Mid Century characteristics, this tranquil Los Angeles home is conveniently located yet seemingly a world away.

Among others, amenities include a beautiful library, a massive soundproof gym/spa flex space that could be converted to a music studio, an architecturally stunning staircase that leads into the basement to enjoy the home theater and entertainment space. This French Chateau must be seen to truly recognize the detail and beauty of this once in a lifetime estate. Also available for short term lease!

Situated on a private cul-de-sac with over 16, 329 sqft of land surrounded by towering trees and grand estates, this rental offers a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of LA. Enjoy easy access to nearby shopping, dining, and beaches while embracing the sought-after Brentwood lifestyle.Not only does this property offer a tranquil escape from the city, it also comes with all the conveniences you need. The large 2-car garage has ample storage space, and the attached workshop offers even more room to store your tools or pursue your hobbies. With the garage, workshop and the home all under one roof, you have everything you need to make this house your own. Plus, the large yard and sparkling pool provide the perfect outdoor escape for nature lovers. Soak up the sun, take a dip, or simply lounge in the peaceful surroundings. This rental truly has it all.

Are you dreaming of a peaceful hilltop hideaway tucked away from city life below, where time stands still and the stars at night are reminiscent of Joshua Tree, where on a full moon the gardens are bathed in moonlight.... This one-of-a-kind artists retreat featured in Architectural Digest was once owned by famed artist Edward Ruscha who reconstructed the footprint. Since then, invited artists have brushed the property with their artistic strokes further enhancing the creative environment. Set amongst the backdrop of the Santa Monica conservancy in Brentwood, the nearly 2-acre property is surrounded by spectacular cactus gardens, trickling fountains, meandering trails, towering palm trees and an array of wide open spaces designed to provide ultimate relaxation. The gated compound consists of a single-level 5750 Square Ft Ranch house, a 600 Sq Ft 1-bedroom guest house and a meditation studio sitting atop the property and looking down onto the billowing landscape below. The main house offers 3 bedrooms on opposing sides of the house, including a primary suite overlooking the pool & grounds, 4.5 bathrooms, a fabulous farm-style eat-in kitchen w/center island, formal dining room, living room, library, den and numerous fireplaces creating a warm ambience. High ceilings and windows surround the dwelling for views of the outdoors from every direction. Outdoor spaces include a large covered patio for lounging & dining, outdoor BBQ area and a salt-water pool with heath ceramics and a diving board. You must agree to share your space with the local wildlife, owls hooting, falcons, parakeets and humming birds carry on, while bicyclists wind their way up and down the peaceful slope of Mandeville Canyon. Great neighbors you will never see! Inquire for lease terms up to 1-year, offered furnished only. Available mid June 2023. Shown by appointment only.

Traditional Westwood Hills home was delicately renovated to balance its original 1940's architecture with today's comforts. Relish coming home to a delightful, bright, and vibrant retreat accentuated with designer finishes, stylish lighting, and wonderful indoor/outdoor flow. The home features a gas-burning fireplace in the living room, three bedrooms upstairs, one bedroom downstairs ideal for guests or office, hardwood floors throughout, central AC, formal dining room, and an exquisitely designed kitchen with a concealed Sub-Zero refrigerator, Wolf range, dishwasher, and wine fridge. Inviting backyard with multiple areas for entertaining or simply relaxing makes this the perfect setting to enjoy time with your guests. The courtyard offers a beautifully designed pergola with wall mounted heat lamps, outdoor TV area, and access to an open-air BBQ and kitchen island. To complete this splendid garden is an L-shaped built-in bench, which surrounds the fire pit to ensure the area feels clean and modern, yet welcoming. Property has beautiful curb appeal; it's situated on a quiet street in a highly desirable neighborhood with great schools and within close proximity to Brentwood and Westwood Village.
